<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151780>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–10. Balclutha jafara habitus. (1) male, Colombia, dorsal, IMDx_1020; (2) male paratype, Seychelles, dorsal, NHMUK 013588847; (3) male, Colombia, IMDx_1019; (4) male, Zimbabwe, dorsal, USNMENT01513827; (5) female paratype, Aldabra, dorsal, NHMUK 013588848; (6) male, South Sudan, dorsal, USNMENT01513828; (7) male, Colombia, dorsal, JNZ_AA0474; (8) same, ventral; (9) male, Colombia, lateral, IMDx_1020; (10) male, Colombia, lateral, JNZ_AA0474. Figs. 7–8, 10: images taken of specimen immersed in ethanol." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151780/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151782>
    dc:description "FIGURES 11–13. Balclutha jafara. (11) face, anterior view, male, South Sudan, USNMENT01513828; (12) face, anterolateral view, male, USA: FL: Belle Glade, JNZ_AA0134; (13) sternite VII, female paratype, Aldabra, NHMUK 013588848." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151782/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10151806>
    dc:description "FIGURE 78. Map of the Everglades Agricultural Area showing rice paddy sample locations and numbers of Balclutha species collected in the August, 2021 sampling period. Map by Kate Love and Alicia Lawrence, FDACS, DPI." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10151806/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

